---
import GuideLayout from '../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';

const chapters = [
  { slug: 'sample', title: 'Getting Started' },
  { slug: 'chapter-2', title: 'Advanced Topics' },
  { slug: 'chapter-3', title: 'Best Practices' },
];
---

<GuideLayout 
  title="Getting Started" 
  date={new Date('2024-01-15')}
  tags={['guide', 'tutorial']}
  chapters={chapters}
  currentSlug="sample"
>
  <p>This is a sample guide demonstrating the 3-column layout.</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Guides are multi-chapter documents with navigation on the left and TOC on the right.</p>

  <h2>Layout Structure</h2>
  <p>The guide layout features:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Chapter navigation on the left sidebar</li>
    <li>Main content in the center</li>
    <li>Table of contents on the right</li>
    <li>Previous/Next chapter navigation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Navigation</h3>
  <p>Use the sidebar to jump between chapters, or use the pagination at the bottom.</p>

  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <p>This layout is ideal for comprehensive tutorials and documentation.</p>
</GuideLayout>
